        <scopecontent id="ref9">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The brief Biographical series contains some personal correspondence, memorabilia, and obituaries. The bulk of the collection consists of Recht's unpublished writings, including: 
                <title render="italic">A World to Win</title>, an autobiography (along with several autobiographical fragments) covering Recht's life through the early 1930s, including his travels throughout the Soviet Union, 
                <title render="italic">Selector H. One</title>, a social-satirical historical science fiction novel, an untitled and incomplete novel largely about "Ernest Strohman," an immigrant of Bohemian origin, various poems, two untitled plays dealing with Jewish history, and an early (1907) pamphlet-length non-fiction manuscript, 
                <title render="italic">The Bohemian in America</title>. The published writings consist of several articles dealing with civil rights and Jewish history.</p>
        </scopecontent>
